<br>
- I pull with Malosini, bring mob back to park  61 air pet.  Sick pet on mob, and mob sticks on pet as soon as the pet starts hitting the mob.  Mob never comes over to me.  I can even slow with my enchanter without aggroing the mob.<br>
<br>
- I've pulled more then one on occasion and when I send in the pet, they alway all gang up on my pet.<br>
<br>
At 65 if you want exp giving mobs, you might want to try Hate's Fury.  The area leading it from Nadox has some pretty tough mobs, that can range from 45 to 55.  I've never been in Hate's Fury, but I'm betting the mobs there are even higher.  It is the highest level zone in the expansion.<br>
<br>
Where I've been hunting in LoY has yeilded pretty good loot.  I managed to get a primary/secondary item that had 5 int, 30 mana, 25 hp + resist, and a pair of feet items that have 6 int, 10 int and some other stats.  Mobs were dropping peridots/opals and between 6 to 8pp.  In Dulak's Harbour I got a couple of Diamond class drops in an hour or so.<br>
<br>
Two thumbs up here for the expansion so far. <p>--------------------------<br>
