<br>
Re-read my post, I gave my guesstimated agro regen and the FD'ed non agro regen.  The agro regen I mentioned of 200-240hp/tick was probably a little on the high side (probably more like 150ish/tick), but I based it off my average dps being 40 and when my dps would drop below (to about 30), they would regen more than I was taking off.  30*6=180ish regen/tick.  <br>
<br>
The non agro regen that I guesstimated was 300-400ish range based on my guess that if it took me 5 ticks with 40dps to take 1 bulb of health off them 40(ave dps)*30(seconds or ticks*6)=1200(damage done)-900(health regened)=300 hp/bulb.  The lblues I was looking at were regening 1bulb/tick when non agro'ed.  Which rouhly='s out to non agro regen = 2x agro regen.  <br>
<br>
These were the undead, the flowers, and the shrooms so they weren't getting healed.  Based on what I was seeing w/ regen I wasn't going to even attempt to go near the ogres.  That being said, if you had read what I wrote, you'd have understood why I fd'ed to see non agro regen.<br>
<br>
And yes, I do realize that the ogre's and tougher things might not regen as fast, but kunark gave birth to higher hp mobs, velious gave birth to more mr mobs (?), sol gave birth to ? (sue me, I never solo'ed in SoL), PoP gave birth to insane mob dps.  It would make sence based on SoE's track record has been to make all mobs in an expantion have the same new thing (or the vast majority of them at least), that LoY will end up being known as the high regen expantion.<br>
<br>
