The other night, I was working my way over to the fort with my 51 paladin for his spell quest drop (which I got later on.  Woot!), and I aggroed a light blue diseased drogmar.  No biggie.  Its light blue.  Should be fairly easy to deal with.<br>
Yeah, right.<br>
I barely managed to reduce its hp bar at roughly the same rate it brought mine down, and I was hitting both more often and harder than it was.  Late in the battle, I decided I needed a quick heal, so I decided to toss a greater heal on myself.  I finally managed to get it off after the third cast (interrupted twice), and by the time it landed, the drogmar had regenerated more of its hp bar than I recovered with my cast (roughly two ticks - greater heal has a 4 second cast time, iirc).<br>
And this was a light blue mob.<br>
The regen level on these things is far too high.<br>
